    "created_at": "2014-06-17T00:41:05Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-06-17T00:41:05Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "My only question is: should we wrap all this into a little common utility that we use for third-party dependencies?  Just an idea, because the api is by necessity kind of ugly (since import is a very special keyword that auto-creates variables):\n\n``` python\n\nfrom IPython.foo import require\n\nzmq, tornado = require('zmq', 'tornado')\n```\n\nand have the hypothetical `require` (or whatever) do any reporting/user information we'd like...\n\nI'm not totally convinced, because of the funky syntax, but at the same time, it would help us have a consistent way to provide the end user with easy dependency information.\n"
  },
