    "body": "@fperez - yeah, I also thought about writing a little wrapper function instead of the try-except blocks, but my worry is that it started looking kind of unpythonic - since it was no longer as evidence that, in your example - zmq and tornado are themselves modules.\n\nBouncing off ideas further - what about something like this:\n\n``` python\nfrom IPython.requirements import zmq, tornado\n```\n\nwhere there would be code in requirements that would catch import errors and give more detailed messages?\n"
