    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I guess the point is that when they hit an error, those people won't necessarily know that IPython requirements have changes - they might start thinking \"but wait a minute - is my python path broken or my virtual env not activated, because IPython used to work on master just fine\" - Fernando stumbling over the (really long) jsonschema import error traceback was what prompted this change - since it's also in a non-trivial place - and he suggested we address that in a manner like this.\n"
