    "created_at": "2014-06-17T05:46:46Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-06-17T05:46:46Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The long and daunting message ends on a message of hope: install jsonschema and all will be well.\n\nI hear your concern @takluyver about cluttering every external import, but that's not what this PR proposes. If this starts to get treated like a regular import error (which it is) then there's no information lost and we're not introducing any kind of unmanageable complexity to make this happen.\n\n@fperez  bumped into this, I bumped into this, as did @pmarshwx over in #5979.\n\nAs @minrk pointed out, we already do these kinds of messages for pyzmq and tornado. Between folks running off of master and pip installing ipython without the square brackets optional dependencies, enough developers can get tripped up by this particular import error down the line that it's worth addressing. \n"
  },
