    "created_at": "2014-06-18T00:02:09Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-06-18T00:02:09Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "As @minrk indicated, it's good to have the TB in case there's a nastier problem to debug. The point of the extra message is simply to provide a clear, unambiguous statement to the user: 'the above import error is really a core dependency you're missing, not some accidental  side-error, install the package to fix it'. It conveys _information_ to the user about a choice _we_ have made regarding package X being an actual core dependency.  The traceback is there in case additional debugging is needed, but in most cases those two lines will just get the user unstuck.\n\nGuys, I'm frankly a bit surprised at how much opposition you're raising for this fairly simple fix. This is three lines of help information with no real complexity, algorithmic cost, maintenance burden, etc. If they get a few users get unstuck, it's a good thing.\n\nI understand the need for solid review, but there's also death by a thousand nitpicks. Let's not devolve into that...\n"
  },
